2️⃣ GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation, 2018):-
Origin: European Union (EU):-
Purpose: EU citizens ke personal data privacy ko protect kare.
Focus: Data privacy, consent aur transparency.
Key Principles:-
Lawfulness, Fairness, Transparency: Data collect karne se pehle clear reason aur consent chahiye.
Purpose Limitation: Data sirf declared purpose ke liye use ho.
Data Minimization: Sirf zaruri data collect kare.
Storage Limitation: Data sirf required duration tak rakha jaye.
Integrity & Confidentiality: Data secure aur accurate ho.
Example: Agar kisi EU citizen ka email address collect ho raha hai,
to unke consent ke bina use karna GDPR violation hai.

3️⃣ HIPAA (Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act, 1996);-
Origin: USA
Purpose: Patient ke health data privacy aur security ko protect kare.
Focus: Protected Health Information (PHI) ka confidentiality aur integrity.
Key Points:-
PHI ka unauthorized access, use, aur disclosure illegal hai.
Hospitals, clinics aur unke business partners ko security rules follow karne hote hain.
Data encryption, access control, audit logs, aur backup policies zaruri hain.
Example: Hospital me patient ke medical records ko sirf authorized staff hi access kar sakta hai.
Unauthorized email ya cloud me share karna HIPAA violation hai.

1️⃣ SOX kya hai?
Full Form: Sarbanes-Oxley Act
Year: 2002
Country: USA
Purpose: Companies ke financial reporting aur accounting ko fraud-free, transparent aur reliable banaye.
Target: Mainly public companies (jo stock market me listed hain).

3️⃣ SOX ke main principles (IT aur business dono):-
Internal Controls:-
Company ke financial systems me proper checks & balances ho.
Example: Accounting software me unauthorized changes prevent ho.

Financial Reporting:-
Accurate aur complete financial statements.
Management aur auditors dono responsible hain.

Data Integrity & Security:-
Sab financial records secure, tamper-proof aur traceable hone chahiye.
Logs aur audit trails maintain karna zaruri hai.

Access Control:-
Sirf authorized log hi sensitive financial data access kar saken.

Audit Trails & Logging:-
Har transaction record ho aur easily trackable ho.

Backup & Recovery:-
Financial data ka regular backup aur disaster recovery plan.

Change Management:-
System me koi bhi change approved aur documented ho.
//////////*
()Log / Auditor = वो व्यक्ति जो data verify karta hai.
Ye check karte hain ki financial statements sach hain ya nahi.
Errors, frauds, ya misstatements ko detect karte hain.
Example:-
Company ke CFO ne revenue report banayi.
Independent auditor aata hai aur verify karta hai ki report me koi galat number ya fraud nahi hai.
Agar sab sahi hai → report approve ho jati hai.
Agar galat hai → auditor report me highlight karta hai aur management accountable hota hai.

1️⃣ Reliable:-
Matlab विश्वसनीय ya dependable.
SOX me iska matlab: Financial reports aur accounting data itna accurate ho ki log uspe bharosa kar saken.

2️⃣ Management aur Auditors:-
Management: Company ke top bosses, jaise CEO, CFO, finance team head. Ye log financial statements banate aur approve karte hain.
Auditors: Independent log ya firm jo check karte hain ki financial statements sach hai ya nahi.
Dono ka role important hai: Management prepare karta hai, auditor verify karta hai.

3️⃣ Accountable:-
Matlab जिम्मेदार.
SOX me iska matlab: Agar financial fraud ya error hota hai,
management aur auditors dono legally responsible hote hain.
Example: Agar CFO ne false profit report file ki → unko penalty aur jail tak ho sakta hai.

4️⃣ Financial Data Integrity:-
Matlab financial data ki सटीकता aur सुरक्षितness.
SOX me iska matlab: Data accurate, complete aur tamper-proof ho.
Example: Revenue, expenses aur balance sheet ka data secure ho, koi unauthorized change na ho.

5️⃣ 2️⃣ SOX kyun important hai?
Financial fraud aur corporate scandals (jaise Enron, WorldCom) ke baad USA ne SOX banaya.
Purpose:-
Transparency → Investors aur public ko sach pata chale.
Accountability → Management aur auditors responsible ho.
Data Integrity → Financial data accurate aur secure ho.
